<h3 id="tube-converter">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#tube-converter" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Tube Converter <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.nickvision.tubeconverter"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>An easy-to-use video downloader (yt-dlp frontend).</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@nlogozzo:matrix.org">Nick</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="https://github.com/nlogozzo/NickvisionTubeConverter/releases/tag/2023.4.0">Tube Converter V2023.4.0</a> is here! This week&rsquo;s release features the ability to run downloads in the background (taking advantage of GNOME 44&rsquo;s new background apps API!) as well as many bugs fixed!</p>
<p>Here&rsquo;s the full changelog:</p>
<ul>
<li>Added the ability to run downloads in the background (<em>off by default</em>)</li>
<li>Fixed an issue where extra escape characters were added in video titles</li>
<li>Improved the UX of adding a download</li>
<li>Updated translations (Thanks everyone on Weblate!)

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/04/twig-90/KmANkJcxAMHwGbyROjuPpqXN.png" alt="" />
